# Architecture review

When implementing functionality that may affect how the system is built or deployed:

**Rule:** Review the **[ARCHITECTURE.md](ARCHITECTURE.md)** file. If any implemented functionality **changes the architecture** of the system (e.g. new services, new data stores, new API versioning, new frontend/backend boundaries, new deployment units), update ARCHITECTURE.md to reflect those changes.

**Examples of architecture-changing work:**
- Adding a new backend service or splitting the API
- Introducing a new database, cache, or message queue
- Changing auth strategy (e.g. adding OAuth providers)
- Adding a new client (e.g. a third app) or changing the monorepo layout
- Changing API versioning or breaking the API contract
- Adding translation/i18n served from backend (new endpoint, new responsibility)

Keep ARCHITECTURE.md accurate so that future work and production planning (see PRODUCTION.md) stay aligned with the actual system.
